HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 783
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of David Samuel "Sammy"
Scott of Lawrence County.
WHEREAS, we were greatly saddened to learn of the untimely passing of David Samuel
"Sammy" Scott; and
WHEREAS, Sammy Scott was a self-employed mechanic, a trade that showcased his
remarkable talent and work ethic; his hands were skilled, and his heart was in every project he
undertook; and
WHEREAS, his favorite pastimes included spending time with his children, going to the
beach, and playing the guitar; he also regularly attended Busby Church of God; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Scott's family was of the utmost importance to him; he was a devoted
father to his two adoring sons, Jasper "Mack" Scott and Axl Ray Scott; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his sons, Sammy Scott will be sadly mourned but fondly
remembered by his parents, Tony and Debora Page Scott; his brothers, Daniel Scott, Mason
(Jade) Pippin, and Tyger Sparks; the mother of his children, Madison Barth; and his little
brothers, Christian Barth and Caden Barth; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his maternal grandparents, David "Ray" Scott
and Annie "Jo" Page; his paternal grandparents, Robert Scott, Sam Whitehead, and Leon and
Eloise Peden McMurtrey; and a brother, Zack Patterson; and
WHEREAS, Sammy Scott lived a life that was a testament to the joy and love he brought
to those around him; his presence was a source of strength and comfort to his family and
friends, and his absence will be deeply felt by all who had the pleasure of knowing him; and
HJR0783
011439
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Sammy Scott leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of David Samuel "Sammy" Scott, reflecting fondly
upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with
courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Scott.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
